<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,381,729]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,304,381,406]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Distribution.</emphasis>
Europe north to 
<number box="[507,537,381,405]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="64.0">64</number>
° N, 
<collectingCountry box="[594,686,381,405]" name="Sweden" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Sweden</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[700,786,381,405]" name="Finland" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Finland</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[847,938,382,406]" name="Norway" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Norway</collectingCountry>
, present on British Isles; 
<collectingCountry box="[1238,1319,381,405]" name="Turkey" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Turkey</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1333,1381,382,405]" name="Iran" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Iran</collectingCountry>
, and North Africa (
<bibRefCitation author="Warncke" box="[309,477,417,441]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" refString="Warncke, K. (1992) Die Westpalaarktischen Arten der Bienengattung Sphecodes Latr. (Hymenoptera, Apidae, Halictinae). Bericht der Naturforschenden Gesellschaft Augsburg, 52, 9 - 64." type="journal article" year="1992">
Warncke 
<number box="[417,477,417,441]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="1992.0">1992</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,381,729]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,297,453,478]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Biology.</emphasis>
Common species that usually occurs in semi-open biotopes with shrubs, forest-steppes, steppes, and forest margins. In central Europe widespread, although except for warm sites it is never numerous. This species is a nest cleptoparasite of smaller species of 
<taxonomicName box="[613,732,525,549]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Halictidae</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation box="[744,943,525,549]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" refString="Sick, M., Ayasse, M., Tengo, J., Engels, W., Lubke, G. &amp; Francke, W. (1994) Host-parasite relationship in six species of Sphecodes bees and their Halictid hosts: Nest intrusion, intranidal behavior, and Dufour's gland volantiles (Hymenoptera: Halictidae). Journal of Insect Behavior, 7, 101 - 117." type="journal article">
Sick 
<emphasis box="[802,860,525,549]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">et al.</emphasis>
(
<number box="[877,935,525,549]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="1994.0">1994</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
experimentally proved Stoeckhert’s (
<number box="[1370,1428,525,549]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="1933.0">1933</number>
) finding of 
<taxonomicName authority="Schenck" authorityName="Schenck" box="[277,679,561,585]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Lasioglossum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pauxillum">
<emphasis box="[277,554,561,585]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Lasioglossum pauxillum</emphasis>
(Schenck)
</taxonomicName>
as a host, 
<bibRefCitation author="Westrich" box="[812,996,561,585]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" refString="Westrich, P. (1989) Die Wildbienen Baden-Wurttembergs. Band. 1 und 2. Eugen Ulmer Verlag, Stuttgart, 972 pp." type="book" year="1989">
Westrich (
<number box="[930,989,561,585]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="1989.0">1989</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Vegter" box="[1059,1217,561,586]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" refString="Vegter, K. (1993) Gastheren van enige soorten Sphecodes in Drenthe (Hymenoptera: Apidae). [Hosts of some Sphecodes in Drenthe]. Entomologische Berichten (Amsterdam), 53, 67 - 70. (in Dutch)." type="journal article" year="1993">
Vegter (
<number box="[1151,1209,561,585]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="1993.0">1993</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
mentioned also 
<taxonomicName authority="Schenck" authorityName="Schenck" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Lasioglossum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="punctatissimum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">L. punctatissimum</emphasis>
(Schenck)
</taxonomicName>
as a confirmed host. Other similar species are likely to be hosts as well: 
<taxonomicName authority="Schenck" authorityName="Schenck" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Lasioglossum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadrinotatulum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">L. quadrinotatulum</emphasis>
(Schenck)
</taxonomicName>
recorded as likely host by 
<bibRefCitation author="Alfken" box="[797,964,633,657]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" refString="Alfken, J. D. (1912) Die Bienenfauna von Ostpreussen. Schrift des physisch-okonomischen Vereins in Konigsberg, 53, 114 - 182." type="journal article" year="1912">
Alfken (
<number box="[896,956,633,657]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="1912.0">1912</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Kirby" authorityName="Kirby" box="[981,1264,633,657]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Lasioglossum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nitidiusculum">
<emphasis box="[981,1169,633,657]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">L. nitidiusculum</emphasis>
(Kirby)
</taxonomicName>
by Stoeckhert (
<number box="[159,217,669,693]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="1933.0">1933</number>
) and 
<taxonomicName authority="Smith" authorityName="Smith" box="[279,506,669,693]" class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Lasioglossum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="prasinum">
<emphasis box="[279,414,670,693]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">L. prasinum</emphasis>
(Smith)
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Vegter" box="[546,704,669,694]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" refString="Vegter, K. (1993) Gastheren van enige soorten Sphecodes in Drenthe (Hymenoptera: Apidae). [Hosts of some Sphecodes in Drenthe]. Entomologische Berichten (Amsterdam), 53, 67 - 70. (in Dutch)." type="journal article" year="1993">
Vegter (
<number box="[634,695,669,693]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="1993.0">1993</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. The hosts can be different in parts of the distributional area, as 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Halictidae" genus="Lasioglossum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="prasinum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">L. prasinum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is rare in central but quite common in north-western Europe.
</paragraph>
